Package: frontiermetrics
Type: Package
Title: Deforestation Frontier Metrics
Version: 0.0.9
Authors@R: 
    person("Pablo Yair", "Huais", , "pablo.huais@unc.edu.ar", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-4062-0779"))
Maintainer: Pablo Yair Huais <pablo.huais@unc.edu.ar>
Description: Provides a toolbox to detect and map high-level patterns of deforestation frontiers. These can be defined as the expansion of forest loss in a given area with a high level of spatio-temporal detail Buchadas et al. (2022) <doi:10.1038/s41893-022-00886-9>. We provide functions to calculate, analyze, plot and export deforestation frontier metrics, based on spatio-temporal data of woodland loss and a given study area.
